Author: Kirill_icodarenta
Title: [ANN] | DARENTA | Revolutionizing the CARSHARING Industry |
Body: A brief reminder of the results of the Darenta tokensale: During the token-sale period, sales were carried out through the ICOBox book building platform, which allowed accepting almost 70 different types of crypto currency. Also PROD tokens could be obtained in exchange for ICOS tokens. At the Pre Sale stage, 1,000,000 tokens were sold. At the Pre ICO stage, 1 239 576 tokens were sold. At the ICO stage, 1,384,729 tokens were sold. A total of 3,624,305 tokens were sold. 5,376,000 were transferred to ICOBox for partner services. Some of the tokens were transferred to other partners. Some of the tokens were allocated in Bounty mode. 2 624 000 was transferred to the team. 31,000,000 tokens remain in the ecosystem of our P2P-car sharing. Some of the tokens were bought out and received by Darenta back, thanks to their use in the Android application. The remaining unsold portion of the tokens from the system of the car sharing will not be sold. Now our startup has more than 90 million PROD tokens on hand, which we will not sell: https://etherscan.io/address/0xf5df88d3a6e412c2c0d896278d82661cb271a164

Author: Amanu-Ra
Title: [ANN] | DARENTA | Revolutionizing the CARSHARING Industry |
Body: A little bit about tokens lock-up  Some ICOs send tokens to holders until the end of the ICO, while conducting a bounty company. People get tokens almost for free or with a big discount. Then they go to sell them to an EtherDelta exchange at a price cheaper than on the ICO website. Because of this, the price of tokens falls, no one bought them for the price on the site.  To avoid this, tokens lock-up (freezing) are introduced. A lockup is the period until the end of an ICO when no one receives tokens. Tokens buyers and the team will receive tokens only after the ICO.  The lockup function is also present in our PROD tokens.When you buy tokens on the site https://ico.darenta.io you see the number of tokens that belongs to you. However, you can sell or transfer tokens only after the end of the lock-up.  Members of the bounty program on the site http://bounty.darenta.io can also see their tokens, however their output will be available only after the end of the lap period.

Author: Kirill_icodarenta
Title: [ANN] | DARENTA | Revolutionizing the CARSHARING Industry |
Body: Hi! It's a nice question. Let me answer to you.  After the introduction of the tokens into the service and platform ecosystem, ProducToken (PROD) tokens will be used in calculations for rent and for partners and customers encouragement. Tokens will be used in the discount system. The use of tokens in the service ecosystem will begin no later than 3 months after the completion of the ICO. ProducToken (PROD) will participate in the economy of the service and the ecosystem as follows: • Clients can rent out their vehicles for tokens; • Renting vehicles with tokens, customers can receive a discount for carsharing commission (up to 50%); • Those who wish, can buy a franchise for tokens if they satisfy all necessary conditions; • Those who wish, can participate in a blog-tour around different countries for a certain number of tokens; • Clients can get tokens for the publications in social networks they make during the period, they rent a car; • The company will encourage participants by tokens to receive feedback after the car rental deals; • Clients can get tokens for permission to place an advertisement on their profile pages if an ad was shown a certain amount of times, and there was a required number of conversions. • We`ll organize a referral program - the person who brought a car owner in the service will receive a certain number of tokens if within a week it brought at least one paid deal. After ICO, the platform’s commission for the informational, intermediary and other services provided by Darenta will be set to 20%. This amount will be added to what the car owners indicate in their profiles. The owners who rent out their vehicles with DARENTA platform will still have the right to request the PRICE they want. Before ICO ends, the commission fee for the carsharing transaction is only 1(one) percent. Each customer will be able to reduce the commission fee for the service, by paying with our tokens ProducToken (PROD).

Author: bitkomuser
Title: [ANN] | DARENTA | Revolutionizing the CARSHARING Industry |
Body: Know your customer (KYC) is the process of a business identifying and verifying the identity of its clients.[1] The term is also used to refer to the bank and anti-money laundering regulations which governs these activities. Know your customer processes are also employed by companies of all sizes for the purpose of ensuring their proposed agents, consultants, or distributors are anti-bribery compliant. Banks, insurers and export creditors are increasingly demanding that customers provide detailed anti-corruption due diligence information.  I think that developers mean something like this one: 1) You need to verify your account 2) You trade tokens by yourself on exchange platform 3) You are happy  So it's classic token trading on exchange platform. Why developers select this abbreviation "KYC" - i don't know =)
